HEADWORD: Impasto
<hw>Im*pas"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It. See
<er>Impaste</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Paint.)</fld> <def>The thickness of the
layer or body of pigment applied by the painter to his canvas with
especial reference to the juxtaposition of different colors and tints in
forming a harmonious whole.</def> <rj><au>Fairholt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impasture</ent>⟦br⟧
